lead_paragraph: Gov. Ron DeSantis of Florida, who appears to be preparing to run for president in 2024, has achieved a national platform by leaning into cultural battles. abstract: The podcaster aspires to be an influential thought leader. But his appeal to a mostly male fan base is about more than just his prognostications.
snippet: The podcaster aspires to be an influential thought leader. But his appeal to a mostly male fan base is about more than just his prognostications.
lead_paragraph: Scott Galloway sat in his home studio in Delray Beach, Fla., staring off into space, trying to think of a joke to kick off the 164th episode of his podcast, “The Prof G Show.” His team of producers waited patiently. After a minute of silence, Mr. Galloway, an N.Y.U. marketing professor and business guru, started a riff about people (like him) born in 1964, including Sandra Bullock. He likened her career to Covid — it continues but no one seems to care. (Mr. Galloway used saltier language.)

main: Is Scott Galloway the Howard Stern of the Business World?
print_headline: Is Scott Galloway a Howard Stern for the M.B.A. Set?
